This is a follow-up on #18937.

It mainly addresses issues reported in https://github.com/spack/spack/pull/18937#pullrequestreview-660753294 and https://github.com/spack/spack/pull/18937#pullrequestreview-662028864

@sethrj this enables static libraries also when `+shared` as you suggested in https://github.com/spack/spack/pull/18937#issuecomment-844422013 but I can revert it if it will be the result of the discussion in #18937.

@lrknox there is a couple of issues in the `develop` versions (the best way not to miss any would be to check all lines containing the word `develop`). I think it makes sense to address them upstream.
